message: “Physicians are one of the key groups that can actively find, see and identify these victims while they’re still in the process of being victimized,” says Alan Janssen, DO, the medical director at the emergency department of Genesys Regional Medical Center.

data.description: For victims of human trafficking, a physician visit can be a life-changing event that sets into motion the process of escaping a captive situation.
data.title: Identifying human trafficking victims: How physicians can help - The DO
